{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 92.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at one time, it was quite an arts center, cultural center in Germany back-- way back in the medieval period.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's-- it's a very old city.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they deeply resent the fact that the concentration camp bears the name of their city-- very resentful of that fact.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They said, we don't know why we get blamed for Dachau, we had nothing to do with it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They just-- it was an old military installation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I think it was a munitions factory during World War II, that area with Dachau, and the Germans put that concentration camp there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the present citizens of Dachau are very resentful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There's an interesting sidelight.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "After we took the camp, the citizens of Dachau said, well, we don't know anything about what was going on in there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Well, it's true.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They weren't allowed in there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But there were numerous German soldiers who were partying in Dachau all the time, getting drunk, so they would have had some knowledge.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they saw thousands of people going in there and none coming out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But it's true they had no real personal knowledge.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we rounded up all the citizens we could find in Dachau and made them go through Dachau.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we made them help bury the bodies.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, we had so many thousand bodies not only in Dachau, but on the outskirts.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Just about two or three weeks before the end of the war, Heinrich Himmler, the head of the Gestapo and the SS, one of the cruelest men that ever lived, sent out an order-- I have a copy of it somewhere-- but it says-- and it was directed to all the commandants of the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 56
    }
  ],
